   <h3>Setup and Requirements</h3>
   <div>
      <p>
         You will need to have your Speck plugged in to your computer in order to use the Speck app.  Simply use the USB
         cable supplied with your Speck&mdash;the small plug goes into the Speck, and the larger one goes into the USB
         port on your computer.
      </p>
      <p>
         You will also need to have the <a href="http://www.google.com/chrome/" target="get_chrome">Google Chrome web browser</a> installed on your computer.  The Speck app is a Google
         Chrome app, and, as such, requires Google Chrome to be installed.
      </p>
   </div>
   <h3>Download and Installation</h3>
   <div>
      <p>
         To install the software on your computer, go to the
         <a href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/speck/anchbeboblnigmihhclbdkpdglecnimi">Speck app's page on the Chrome Web Store</a>,
         and then click the "Add To Chrome" button. The videos below demonstrate the download and installation
